I didn’t expect to fall in love with this tiny mountain town, but Dharamkot had other plans✨

Quiet cafés, mostly Israeli travelers, and a pace of life that gently forces you to slow down. I had initially booked my stay in McLeodganj, but once I discovered Dharamkot, I couldn’t help but shift. Four days flew by, and I wish I had stayed just a little longer🤍
